Sales Summary Dashboard 
       Description
The Sales Summary dashboard provides a comprehensive, single-page overview of total sales, purchase values, profit, and quantity sold. The KPIs deliver an instant snapshot of total selling value, total buying value, overall profit, and units sold, offering a clear understanding of current business performance.

The dashboardâ€™s visualization suite enables users to:

    + analyze sales and profit by manufacturer,

    + observe changes in average prices and their impact,

    + understand category-level sales distribution,

    + track daily sales and purchases,

    + break down profit structure and identify its key drivers.

The available filters (Sale Type, Month Name, Payment Mode) make it possible to deepen the analysis and quickly isolate the most important trends based on sales type, time period, and payment methods.  

       Conclusion

This dashboard enables quick assessment of overall sales momentum, identification of high-profit manufacturers and categories, monitoring of the balance between purchases and sales, and detection of daily fluctuations.

It supports better decision-making by helping to.

     + detect sales declines in a timely manner,

     + evaluate the impact of price changes on profitability,

     + improve stock and purchase management,

     + prevent potential future issues by relying on identified trends and patterns.



